The paper deals with data detection in MIMO communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of approximate message passing (AMP) is a technique commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the detection algorithm, which is a topic related to multimedia systems (cs.MM).
